<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum nigrum" order="Solanales" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigrum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Solanum nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is native to Eurasia and has been sporadically introduced and locally naturalised in temperate North America. It is possible that populations from eastern and western areas have different origins (see below).
</paragraph>
